      <article class="post-789 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-accounting category-case-competition category-competition category-deloitte category-kelley-school-of-business category-undergrad tag-araya-stahoviak tag-caroline-short tag-curtis-elliott tag-deloitte-fantaxtic-national-case-study-competition tag-deloitte-university tag-katie-roebuck tag-lewis-cherry tag-sandra-owen tag-steve-kimble tag-tax-cuts-and-jobs-act-of-2017 entry" id="post-789" role="article">
       <header class="entry-header">
        <h2 class="h2 entry-title">
         <a href="https://blog.kelley.iu.edu/2019/01/24/kelley-school-accounting-students-ecstatic-about-winning-the-deloitte-fantaxtic-national-case-study-competition/" rel="bookmark">
          Kelley School accounting students ecstatic about winning the Deloitte FanTAXtic National Case Study Competition
         </a>
        </h2>
        <p class="post-info entry-meta">
         <span class="posted-on">
          Posted on
          <a href="https://blog.kelley.iu.edu/2019/01/24/kelley-school-accounting-students-ecstatic-about-winning-the-deloitte-fantaxtic-national-case-study-competition/" rel="bookmark">
           <time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2019-01-24T21:48:16+00:00">
            January 24, 2019
           </time>
          </a>
         </span>
         <span class="byline">
          by
          <span class="entry-author author">
           <a href="https://blog.kelley.iu.edu/author/vlahakis/">
            George Vlahakis
           </a>
          </span>
         </span>
        </p>
       </header>
       <section class="entry-content">
        <a href="https://blog.kelley.iu.edu/files/2019/01/IMG_3615-1qjh4oo.jpg">
        </a>
        <a href="https://blog.kelley.iu.edu/files/2019/01/IMG_3615-1qjh4oo.jpg">
         <img alt="" class="aligncenter wp-image-802 size-large" height="480" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" src="https://blog.kelley.iu.edu/files/2019/01/IMG_3615-1qjh4oo-1024x768.jpg" srcset="https://blog.kelley.iu.edu/files/2019/01/IMG_3615-1qjh4oo-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https://blog.kelley.iu.edu/files/2019/01/IMG_3615-1qjh4oo-300x225.jpg 300w, https://blog.kelley.iu.edu/files/2019/01/IMG_3615-1qjh4oo-768x576.jpg 768w" width="640"/>
        </a>
        <p>
        </p>
        <p>
         BLOOMINGTON, Ind. – Many accountants still are determining how the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act of 2017 impacts clients. Advising clients on tax planning related to the new law was at the heart of a case adeptly handled last weekend by students in Indiana University’s Kelley School of Business.
        </p>
        <p>
         The Kelley School team took top honors at the 18th Annual Deloitte FanTAXtic National Case Study Competition, defeating eight other business schools that sent student teams to the finals. In all, nearly 60 teams representing more than 40 colleges and universities participated in regional qualifier events at Deloitte offices throughout the country in early November.
        </p>
        <p>
         This was the second year that Kelley has sent a team to the competition and the first time it competed in this national competition. Other national finalists included second-place finisher, the University of Illinois-Chicago; third-place team Syracuse University and Fordham University, the University of Nebraska, North Carolina State University, the University of Northern Iowa, Texas A&amp;M University and the University of Utah.
        </p>
        <p>
         “Our Kelley team was amazing,” said Sandra Owen, senior lecturer of accounting and the Kelley team’s faculty advisor. “Although only one of the students had even taken a tax class, they were able to research and understand the relevant tax law, including some challenging new tax provisions, apply it to their client’s situation, and explain their analysis and recommendations clearly and concisely to the client.
        </p>
        <p>
         “I am so impressed with how well they performed, especially under the tight time constraints at the national competition, and how well they worked together as a team,” she added.
        </p>
        <p>
         <a class="more-link" href="https://blog.kelley.iu.edu/2019/01/24/kelley-school-accounting-students-ecstatic-about-winning-the-deloitte-fantaxtic-national-case-study-competition/#more-789">
          <span aria-label="Continue reading Kelley School accounting students ecstatic about winning the Deloitte FanTAXtic National Case Study Competition">
           (more…)
          </span>
         </a>
        </p>
        <div addthis:title="Kelley School accounting students ecstatic about winning the Deloitte FanTAXtic National Case Study Competition " addthis:url="https://blog.kelley.iu.edu/2019/01/24/kelley-school-accounting-students-ecstatic-about-winning-the-deloitte-fantaxtic-national-case-study-competition/" class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style ">
         <a class="addthis_button_facebook_like" fb:like:layout="button_count">
         </a>
         <a class="addthis_button_tweet">
         </a>
         <a class="addthis_counter addthis_pill_style">
